data.title: Nalbandian in doubt for Open
data.text:
Argentinian David Nalbandian's Australian Open campaign is in disarray after the tennis star suffered a back injury during practice today.

Nalbandian, who twice beat World No.1 Roger Federer last year, was hit by back spasms while practising with Russian Marat Safin at Melbourne Park.

He has been forced to pull out of the Kooyong Classic and is scheduled to have MRI scans later today.
